                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">How hard would it be for soe to put a big pinch in the PA/Plat Sales business?
<br />

<br />
Here's what they could do:
<br />

<br />
1) Log Large movements of platinum between accounts  <img src="images/smiles/icon_idea.gif" alt="icon_idea.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />
2) Buy some platinum of a given server  <img src="images/smiles/icon_lol.gif" alt="icon_lol.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />
3) Track the platinum back to its "bank"  <img src="images/smiles/icon_eek.gif" alt="icon_eek.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />
4) Watch where platinum from the "bank" goes  <img src="images/smiles/icon_cool.gif" alt="icon_cool.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />
5) Remove the platinum from the accounts it winds up in <img src="images/smiles/icon_redface.gif" alt="icon_redface.gif" border="0" />   Targetting the PA's customers will be more effective than targeting the PA.
<br />
6) Request a refund for the plat SOE bought, because the PA didn't provide the service they advertised   <img src="images/smiles/icon_twisted.gif" alt="icon_twisted.gif" border="0" />.  Sue them if neccessary to get that refund.
<br />

<br />
Why do it this way.  People who lose the plat they bought from PAs will want their money back. That many refunds would put a pinch in their business, and publicizing it would warn people off from buying it in the first place.  If the PAs don't refund the money, word of that will get out and help shut them down.
<br />

<br />
So what do they need, a little bit of coding, some log space and a few people to do this on occasion.  I think that even as few as two people put on this at SOE could make a huge difference.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 9px; line-height: normal"><span style="color: darkred">Iumarex Mistweaver
<br />
Coercer for Greater Druids
<br />
Quellious</span></span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
