                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I don't have a problem with people going online and exchanging goods and services.  Why should SoE discourage attention and value given to their online games, when they can publicly discourage it and privately rejoice in it?
<br />

<br />
The fact that people are willing to pay real dollars for game currency shows they're onto something.  Why punish people for ingenuity and creativity?
<br />

<br />
Heck, I don't like the inflation either.  But when you get into the Planes your real drops are No Drop most the time, the good ones anyway.  The bazaar really doesn't affect you unless you're a tradeskiller, then, so what difference does it really make how overpriced bazaar junk is?
<br />

<br />
If everything is overpriced, then don't buy it... if no one does, then the price will come down.  Personally, the bazaar has very little to offer me anyway.
<br />

<br />
My advice? Just play for your drops and stop worrying about what other players do with their stuff and plat.  You'll have much more fun.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
