<br />
Because the conversion of in-game artifacts to real-life cash attracts and encourages RL scammers and crooks to try to find and use exploits in the game.
<br />

<br />
Face it, if all you could get in from an exploit was a bazillion plat or  a Longsword of Uberness, SOE would only have to defend against in game cheaters (and there are enough of them).  Given the cash incentive, thought, SOE has to try to defend against any schmuck with a computer anywhere in the world that can figure out how to get in the game.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
