                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">A few over educated words ....
<br />

<br />
Yes, the marginal utility of a PP has gone down and thus it's relative buying power in term of high end items has diminished.  For example: If you have one beer, you prize it and would not be willing to give it to a stranger for a cigarette.  If you have a case of beer you may be willing to give 2 beers for the same cigarette from the stranger.  Pre-Kunark everyone had 1-2 beers and seeing items sell for 10K was rare.  Today people have a keg and items are getting tot he over 500K mark.  We have a game where plat leaves the game at a very slow rate.  If there where a way for plat to leave the game at the same rate that it is coming in the relative utility would become static and the buying power related to it would stabilize. 
<br />

<br />
I really wish they, Verant/Sony would fix the loop holes by which plat is being created, it is ruining the game IMHO.  
<br />

<br />
As for PA, MySS or any other avenue for selling in game items for anything other than in game currency/items, VI had a policy once that did NOT allow these sales and Sony seems to not willing to react but I would rather see them go away and return the pride of wearing X item or reaching level 65 back to having had to earn it rather than just plopping down some RL cash.  Remember that there is no difference between can't and won't.
<br />

<br />
For those of you that don't know who VI is/was ........it's Sony today.
<br />

<br />
I remember the pride of weilding a ghoulbane that I camped.
<br />
I remember the pride of wearing a full suit of bronze.
<br />
I remember the honor......</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-style: italic"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal"><span style="color: green">Master Finbarr</span></span></span>
<br />
E Marr</span>
