                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I play EQ to have fun.  It's a game, with rules and objectives and interaction with other players.  
<br />

<br />
If I bought plat or levels or anything outside the game I wouldn't be really "playing" the game.  It's equivalent to using the cheat codes on a console or god mode in Quake.  It's equivalent to giving up and saying "Yes I can't get these items or levels by myself by playing the game...so I'm gonna buy em".  
<br />

<br />
If these people had no effect on my playing the game, I would not care.   
<br />

<br />
Unfortunately everyone is in the same game since it is a multiplayer game.  I enjoy using my hard earned plat to buy stuff.  Give my character a new pair of shoes.  Thats a little bit of the fun.  If I goto the bazaar and see those shoes are all of a sudden going to cost my character 300K...it's annoying.  If the increase in prices is caused by the people buying plat and paying more than they should because they just got 1million plat for cash....well then...that sucks too.   
<br />

<br />
So anyone I find out who is playing the game with outside "cheats"...I just stick em on ignore.  They aren't playing the same game as me, so I'm not interested in playing with them.  
<br />

<br />
OOt.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
